# .gitignore

# Purpose:
# This file specifies intentionally untracked files that Git should ignore.
# Files already tracked by Git are not affected; use `git rm --cached` to stop tracking.
# Use it to exclude sensitive information, dependencies, build output, and more,
# enhancing security and keeping the repository clean and lightweight.

# Usage:
# - Single file: FileName.ext
# - Entire directory: DirName/
# - Ignore patterns: *.log, !important.log (exclude all .log files except important.log)


